    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Ginkgo biloba are attributed to its antioxidant activity, which helps protect cells from oxidative damage and prevent chronic diseases. Its neuroprotective effects are due to the presence of flavonoids, which have been shown to inhibit the formation of beta-amyloid plaques associated with Alzheimer's disease. The anti-inflammatory properties of Ginkgo biloba are mediated by saponins, which have been found to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines. Additionally, its cardioprotective effects are thought to be a result of the bioactive compounds' ability to improve blood flow and reduce platelet aggregation, thereby reducing the risk of cardiovascular disease. Furthermore, the antimicrobial properties of Ginkgo biloba are attributed to the presence of volatile oils, which have been shown to exhibit antibacterial and antifungal activity.",
