    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Ginkgo biloba are flavonoids such as quercetin and kaempferol which have antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, and ginkgolides including ginkgolide a and ginkgolide b which act as platelet activating factor antagonists inhibiting blood clot formation. Bilobalide is a triterpene lactone that protects neurons from damage and promotes neural function. Proanthocyanidins, also present in Ginkgo biloba, have been shown to exhibit antioxidant and free radical scavenging activities. Additionally, flavonoids like isorhapontigenin possess neuroprotective and anti-inflammatory properties. These constituents contribute to Ginkgo biloba's therapeutic effects in improving cognitive function, memory, and blood flow.",
