    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Ginkgo biloba are standardized extracts and teas made from its leaves. Ginkgo biloba tea is a liquid extract brewed from dried Ginkgo leaves, typically used for its antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. Ginkgo biloba extract tincture and ginkgo biloba capsules contain highly concentrated standardized extracts of flavonoids and terpenoids, which are more bioavailable than teas. Ginkgo biloba tincture is a concentrated liquid extract made from the leaves, often used for its cognitive-enhancing and blood-flow-improving properties. Ginkgo biloba oil is a carrier oil infused with Ginkgo extracts, commonly used in topical applications for its anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects.",
