    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Ginkgo biloba improperly are bleeding complications, including experience bleeding due to its antiplatelet properties, which can interact with warfarin, an anticoagulant medication, and increase the risk of bleeding. Individuals may also develop allergic reactions to Ginkgo biloba, such as skin rashes or respiratory issues. Furthermore, improper use of Ginkgo biloba can also lead to increased bleeding risk, particularly in individuals with bleeding disorders or those taking medications that thin the blood. Additionally, some people may experience headaches due to Ginkgo biloba's vasodilatory effects, which can cause blood vessels to dilate and lead to discomfort. These side effects are often associated with high doses of Ginkgo biloba or prolonged use."
